Interface Catalog


  • public interface Catalog
    Top level Catalog APIs that supports table DDLs and namespace listing.

                  Schema schema,
                  PartitionSpec spec,
                  java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> tableProperties)
        creates the table or throws AlreadyExistsException.
        Parameters:

        schema - the schema for this table, can not be null.
        spec - the partition spec for this table, can not be null.
        tableProperties - can be null or empty

      • tableExists

        Check if table exists or not.
        Parameters:
        tableIdentifier - an identifier to identify this table in a namespace.
        Returns:
        true if table exists, false if it doesn't.

      • dropTable

        void dropTable(TableIdentifier tableIdentifier)
        Drops the table if it exists, otherwise throws NoSuchTableException The implementation should not delete the underlying data but ensure that a subsequent call to tableExists(TableIdentifier) returns false.

        If the table does not exists it will throw NoSuchTableException

        Parameters:
        tableIdentifier - an identifier to identify this table in a namespace.

      • renameTable

        void renameTable(TableIdentifier from,
                 TableIdentifier to)
        Renames a table. If from does not exists throws NoSuchTableException If to exists than throws AlreadyExistsException.
        Parameters:
        from - original name of the table.
        to - expected new name of the table.
